'''Localeze''', a service of [[Neustar]], is a [[content manager]] for [[Local search (Internet)|local search]] engines. The company provides businesses with tools to verify and manage the identity of their local listings across the Web. The company works with local search platform partners and location-based <ref>{{cite web|last=Diana |first=Alison |url=http://www.informationweek.com/news/software/soa_webservices/showArticle.jhtml?articleID=228800018&cid=RSSfeed_IWK_News |title=Twitter Expands Places Dataset |publisher=InformationWeek |date=2010-12-09 |accessdate=2013-09-14}}</ref> service partners, national brands and local business clients.<ref name="MediaPost News1">{{cite news|url=http://www.mediapost.com/publications/?fa=Articles.showArticle&art_aid=121441|title=Microsoft's Bing Anchors On Localeze Business Data|last=Sullivan|first=Laurie|date=2010-01-28|publisher=MediaPost News|accessdate=23 March 2010}}</ref><ref>[http://directmag.com/sem/news/moneytree-localeze-search-local-1103/ ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101121093756/http://directmag.com/sem/news/moneytree-localeze-search-local-1103/ |date=November 21, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Rao |first=Leena |url=https://techcrunch.com/2010/09/28/tello-gives-businesses-consumer-feedback-on-the-fly/ |title=Tello Gives Businesses Consumer Feedback On The Fly |publisher=TechCrunch |date=2010-09-28 |accessdate=2013-09-14}}</ref>

==History==
Localeze was created in 2005 to help businesses ensure that they have accurate name, address and phone number data available on [[Web search engine|search engines]], [[Yellow pages|Internet Yellow Pages]] and vertical directories.  

In 2010, business listings were also included in [[Personal navigation assistant|personal navigation devices]],<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,2367330,00.asp | work=PC Magazine | first=Mark | last=Hachman | title=TomTom Adds Business POIs via Localeze Deal | date=3 August 2010}}</ref> [[Mobile application development|mobile apps]] and on [[social networking service]]s.<ref>{{cite web|last=Eldon |first=Eric |url=http://www.insidefacebook.com/2010/08/20/how-marketers-and-businesses-can-start-using-facebook-places/ |title=How Marketers and Businesses Can Start Using Facebook Places |publisher=Inside Facebook |date=2010-08-20 |accessdate=2013-09-14}}</ref>

==Product description==
As a local search business listings provider, Localeze collects and distributes business listings that can be verified by businesses themselves.  Its business listings are used by search, social and mobile companies<ref>{{cite web|last=Rao |first=Leena |url=https://techcrunch.com/2010/02/24/chacha-gets-into-the-local-business-listings-game/ |title=ChaCha Gets Into The Local Business Listings Game |publisher=TechCrunch |date=2010-02-24 |accessdate=2013-09-14}}</ref> in the domain of Local Search and [[location-based service]]s. Such partners include [[Yahoo!]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neustar.biz/infoservices/solutions/localeze/businesses/our-distribution-network |title=Our Distribution Network |publisher=Neustar |accessdate=2013-09-14}}</ref> [[Bing (search engine)|Bing]], [[Yellow pages|Yellow Pages]], [[TomTom]], [[Siri]] (acquired by [[Apple Inc.|Apple]]), [[Twitter]] and [[Facebook]].<ref name="Search Engine Land 2">{{cite news|url=http://searchengineland.com/making-sense-of-facebook-places-48987|title=Making Sense of Facebook Places|date=2010-08-19|publisher=Search Engine Land|accessdate=20 August 2010}}</ref>

